Today i learnt Mini project:
Let‚Äôs build a Battleship-style 
game: ‚ÄúSink a Dot Com‚Äù
Goal:
Sink all three of the computer‚Äôs Dot Coms in the fewest guesses. You get a rating at the end based on performance.

Grid:
	‚Ä¢	Virtual 7x7 grid (rows: A-G, columns: 0-6).
	‚Ä¢	Three Dot Coms, each occupying 3 consecutive cells.

Gameplay:
	‚Ä¢	Player enters a guess like A3 or C5.
	‚Ä¢	Computer responds with:
	    ‚Ä¢	Hit ‚Üí part of a Dot Com is hit.
	    ‚Ä¢	Miss ‚Üí nothing hit
	    ‚Ä¢	You sunk [DotComName] ‚Üí entire Dot Com is destroyed
	‚Ä¢	Game ends when all three Dot Coms are sunk.

<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<----------- MY code-------->>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
                import java.util.*;

public class SinkADotComEasy {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        Random rand = new Random();

        int gridSize = 7;

        // Step 1: Place one DotCom of size 3 horizontally
        int row = rand.nextInt(gridSize);
        int col = rand.nextInt(gridSize - 2); // ensure it fits in row

        // Store DotCom cells in a simple array
        String[] dotCom = new String[3];
        for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
            dotCom[i] = "" + (char)('A' + row) + (col + i);
        }

        int numOfGuesses = 0;
        int hits = 0;

        System.out.println("Welcome to Sink a Dot Com!");
        System.out.println("A DotCom is hiding on a 7x7 grid (rows A-G, cols 0-6).");
        System.out.println("Try to sink it by guessing cells like A3, C5, etc.");

        // Step 2: Play until all 3 cells are hit
        while (hits < 3) {
            System.out.print("Enter your guess: ");
            String guess = sc.nextLine().trim().toUpperCase();
            numOfGuesses++;

            boolean hit = false;
            for (int i = 0; i < dotCom.length; i++) {
                if (dotCom[i] != null && dotCom[i].equals(guess)) {
                    System.out.println("Hit!");
                    dotCom[i] = null; // mark as hit
                    hits++;
                    hit = true;
                    break;
                }
            }

            if (!hit) {
                System.out.println("Miss");
            }
        }

        System.out.println("You sunk the DotCom! üéâ");
        System.out.println("You took " + numOfGuesses + " guesses.");
    }
}
